Method Detail

matches

public boolean matches(URI uri)
Returns true if the URI matches this pattern. If successful, the variable values are available by calling getLastMatch() (not thread safe).

Parameters:
uri - a String to check against this pattern.
Returns:
true if the String matches this pattern

matches

public boolean matches(String uri)
                throws URISyntaxException

Throws:

getMatch

public Map<String,String> getMatch(URI uri)
Returns results from parsing a URI with this pattern. If the URI doesn't match the pattern, this will return null.

Parameters:
uri - A URI to match against this URIPattern
Returns:
A Map of the pattern's variable names to values from the parsed URI

getLastMatch

public Map<String,String> getLastMatch()
Returns the parsed results of the last matched URI. Not thread-safe. This is intended as a convenience for single-threaded callers that want to use matches() and not re-parse the URI to get the result.

Returns:
a result map from the last successful match
